  "text": "where χ is a potential for the 4-velocity of CDM, U µ = −g µν ∂ ν χ, and ρ is the energy density. The latter acts as a Lagrange multiplier whose variation ensures that U µ U µ = −1. Variation with respect to χ gives the continuity equation ∇ µ (ρ∂ µ χ) = 0 while variation of the CDM part of the action with respect to g µν gives the usual CDM energy momentum tensor T µν = ρU µ U ν . Gravity is described by the standard Einstein-Hilbert term with the addition of a cosmological constant with [CITATION_1] R the 4-dimensional Ricci Scalar, and κ = 8πG. The ADM decomposition for the metric can now be used to develop a Hamiltonian formalism for this system. Writing the metric as",
